    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rules_title",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 610,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 20,
      "text": "Non-negotiable Security Rules (PRD 4, 6, 9):",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#1a1615",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "originalText": "Non-negotiable Security Rules (PRD 4, 6, 9):",
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rules",
      "x": 120,
      "y": 635,
      "width": 780,
      "height": 100,
      "text": "4.1 Tenant isolation: every table has RLS on auth.uid() -- no exceptions\n4.2 OAuth tokens: encrypted in Vault, never in client, server-only refresh\n4.3 Email bodies: encrypted at rest, decrypted per-request in edge function memory\n4.3 PII redaction: email bodies NEVER in logs, fixtures, or observability\n4.4 Auto-send: hard floor 0.85 confidence -- user can raise, never lower\n9.1 Cross-tenant aggregation: forbidden in v1, even anonymised\n9.4 Service-role: never in user-facing endpoints\n9.6 Refresh token rotation: server-only, never in client JavaScript",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#ef4444",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "originalText": "",
      "autoResize": true
    }
  ],
